''Theorem.''
A solution $$x\colon \openI{t_0,t_1} \to V$$ can be continued to the right if and only if the limit $$x_1 \coloneqq \lim_{t \nearrow t_1} x(t)$$ exists and $$(t_1,x_1) \in G.$$

